Perfect — that’s the clean way in Power Pages.

Here’s how to structure it when you have an **external JS Web File** (e.g., `/poh-intake.js`) and **external CSS** (e.g., `/poh-intake.css`). I’m also updating the HTML so it’s easy to target with IDs/classes, and the JS handles the same behavior (show/hide tools list based on radio).

---

## 1) HTML (page code) — keep it mostly markup only

```html
<div class="poh-page">

  <section class="poh-section">
    <h2 class="poh-section-title">General Questions</h2>

    <div class="poh-form">

      <!-- Division -->
      <div class="poh-row">
        <label class="poh-label" for="division">Division</label>
        <div class="poh-field">
          <select id="division" class="poh-select">
            <option value="">Select division</option>
            <option selected>1L Financial Crimes Risk</option>
            <option>Operations</option>
            <option>Technology</option>
            <option>Compliance</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Support type -->
      <div class="poh-row">
        <label class="poh-label">What type of support are you looking for today?*</label>

        <div class="poh-field poh-radio-group" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Support type">
          <label class="poh-radio">
            <input type="radio" name="supportType" value="general" />
            <span>General Query</span>
          </label>

          <label class="poh-radio">
            <input type="radio" name="supportType" value="usecase" checked />
            <span>I have a use case to submit</span>
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tool / approach (checkbox list) -->
      <div class="poh-row" id="toolRow">
        <label class="poh-label">Which tool or approach are you interested in</label>

        <div class="poh-field poh-checklist" role="group" aria-label="Tool or approach">
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Copilot Studio"> <span>Copilot Studio</span></label>
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Automation using UiPath"> <span>Automation using UiPath</span></label>
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Automation using Power Automate or Power Apps"> <span>Automation using Power Automate or Power Apps</span></label>
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Process Mining or Task Mining using Celonis"> <span>Process Mining or Task Mining using Celonis</span></label>
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Workflow Management"> <span>Workflow Management</span></label>
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Process Re-Engineering"> <span>Process Re-Engineering</span></label>
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Design Thinking"> <span>Design Thinking</span></label>
          <label class="poh-check"><input type="checkbox" value="Unsure/Other"> <span>I am unsure or looking for something else</span></label>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</div>

<!-- Link your external CSS + JS web files -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/poh-intake.css" />
<script src="/poh-intake.js" defer></script>
```

> ✅ In Power Pages, your Web File must be published and accessible at that URL path.

---

## 2) `poh-intake.js` (external JS Web File)

```javascript
(function () {
  function qs(sel, root) { return (root || document).querySelector(sel); }
  function qsa(sel, root) { return Array.from((root || document).querySelectorAll(sel)); }

  function toggleTools() {
    const toolRow = qs("#toolRow");
    const selected = qs('input[name="supportType"]:checked')?.value;
    if (!toolRow) return;

    toolRow.style.display = (selected === "usecase") ? "flex" : "none";

    // Optional: if hidden, clear checkboxes
    if (selected !== "usecase") {
      qsa('#toolRow input[type="checkbox"]').forEach(cb => cb.checked = false);
    }
  }

  function init() {
    // Bind change events
    qsa('input[name="supportType"]').forEach(r => {
      r.addEventListener("change", toggleTools);
    });

    // Initial state
    toggleTools();
  }

  // Ensure DOM is ready (defer usually enough, this is extra-safe)
  if (document.readyState === "loading") {
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", init);
  } else {
    init();
  }
})();
```

---

## 3) `poh-intake.css` (external CSS Web File)

```css
.poh-page{
  max-width: 1100px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 10px;
  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;
  color:#1a1a1a;
}

.poh-section-title{
  font-size: 32px;
  font-weight: 650;
  margin: 0 0 18px;
}

.poh-form{ max-width: 900px; }

.poh-row{
  display:flex;
  align-items:flex-start;
  gap: 24px;
  padding: 12px 0;
}

.poh-label{
  width: 330px;
  text-align: right;
  font-size: 14px;
  color:#333;
  margin: 0;
  padding-top: 6px;
}

.poh-field{ flex: 1; }

.poh-select{
  width: 520px;
  max-width: 100%;
  height: 36px;
  padding: 6px 10px;
  border: 1px solid #cfcfcf;
  border-radius: 4px;
  background:#fff;
  font-size: 14px;
}

.poh-radio-group,
.poh-checklist{
  display:flex;
  flex-direction:column;
  gap: 10px;
  padding-top: 2px;
}

.poh-radio,
.poh-check{
  display:flex;
  align-items:center;
  gap: 10px;
  font-size: 14px;
}

@media (max-width: 820px){
  .poh-row{ flex-direction: column; }
  .poh-label{ width: 100%; text-align:left; }
}
```

---

## 4) Common Power Pages gotchas (so your JS actually runs)

* If your Web File is not loading, open DevTools → **Network** and check:

  * `GET /poh-intake.js` returns **200**, not 404.
* In Power Pages, sometimes the file path becomes:

  * `/poh-intake.js` **or** `/-/media/poh-intake.js` (depends on how it’s uploaded/published).
* If you use jQuery in your org, you can— but the above is plain JS.

---

If you paste your **exact Web File URL** (the one that loads in browser), I’ll adjust the `<script src>` and `<link href>` to match your portal’s correct path so it works first try.

